{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"lxfnzfx9x4xdx3pxjcvt5lq","title":"Object Cloning in Java","desc":"","updated":1713644137262,"created":1712939265697,"custom":{},"fname":"lang.java.paradigms.oo.objects.cloning","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":".","selfContained":true,"name":"cs"},"contentHash":"2f563de0b553c7c0657da6c567888fee","links":[{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"lang.java.paradigms.oo.objects.cloning","id":"lxfnzfx9x4xdx3pxjcvt5lq","vaultName":"cs"},"value":"paradigm.oo.components.object.cloning","position":{"start":{"line":4,"column":11,"offset":13},"end":{"line":4,"column":52,"offset":54},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"paradigm.oo.components.object.cloning"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"lang.java.paradigms.oo.objects.cloning","id":"lxfnzfx9x4xdx3pxjcvt5lq","vaultName":"cs"},"value":"Object","position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":33,"offset":261},"end":{"line":11,"column":43,"offset":271},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"Object"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"lang.java.paradigms.oo.objects.cloning","id":"lxfnzfx9x4xdx3pxjcvt5lq","vaultName":"cs"},"value":"tags.not allowed by default","position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":20,"offset":334},"end":{"line":13,"column":51,"offset":365},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"tags.not allowed by default"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"lang.java.paradigms.oo.objects.cloning","id":"lxfnzfx9x4xdx3pxjcvt5lq","vaultName":"cs"},"value":"lang.java.lib.interfaces.marker.cloneable","position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":135,"offset":449},"end":{"line":13,"column":180,"offset":494},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"lang.java.lib.interfaces.marker.cloneable"}}],"anchors":{},"children":[],"parent":"vjlml1i0r5gbl63eo95uljb","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"object-cloning-in-java\">Object Cloning in Java<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#object-cloning-in-java\"></a></h1>\n<p>The usual <a href=\"/cs/notes/3y962961axl79uijuaseom8\">Object Cloning</a> ways work just as well in Java. However, clone() method is much easier and can be used to overcome the limitations of those methods.</p>\n<pre class=\"language-java\"><code class=\"language-java\"><span class=\"token class-name\">A</span> obj1 <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token class-name\">A</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> obj<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">clone</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n</code></pre>\n<p><code>clone</code> is a member function of <a title=\"Private\" href=\"https://wiki.dendron.so/notes/hfyvYGJZQiUwQaaxQO27q.html\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"private\">Object (Private)</a> which throws an exception when used. Why?</p>\n<p>Cloning a class is <a class=\"color-tag\" style=\"--tag-color: #419c03;\" href=\"/cs/notes/pjx7u5gpwn38wpf3pvna8sj\">not allowed by default</a> for security reasons. But if the class itself allows you i.e. the class implements <a href=\"/cs/notes/6fe2bcmqj3rdsd3wd82k3lp\">Cloneable</a>, then you can use <code>clone()</code> method.</p>","noteIndex":{"id":"7ncn3al6mmutkhgoesulce9","title":"Computer Science","desc":"","updated":1715103618849,"created":1713296516553,"custom":{"nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"},"fname":"root","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":".","selfContained":true,"name":"cs"},"contentHash":"36faf26c6be438d4aed355d72b55a110","links":[{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"7ncn3al6mmutkhgoesulce9","vaultName":"cs"},"value":"arch","position":{"start":{"line":6,"column":3,"offset":105},"end":{"line":6,"column":11,"offset":113},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"arch"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"7ncn3al6mmutkhgoesulce9","vaultName":"cs"},"value":"paradigm","position":{"start":{"line":11,"column